<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-damaged" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Damaged characters</head>
    <p>Character or characters damaged on the source document, but not sufficiently ambiguous to require
        tagging as <gi>unclear</gi>.</p>
    <p><specList>
            <specDesc key="damage"/>
        </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p>

    <p>Damaged but legible characters should be enclosed in a <gi>damage</gi> element.</p>

    <p>No Leiden equivalent (although some conventions would indiscriminately use underdots for damaged
        letters even if they are perfectly legible; this is not recommended).</p>    

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london">
        <damage>abc</damage>
    </egXML>

    

    <div xml:id="trans-damage-responsibility">
        <head>Responsibility for this section</head>
        <listBibl>
            <bibl><respStmt><resp>author</resp><name>Gabriel Bodard</name></respStmt></bibl>
        </listBibl>
    </div>
</div>
